# ██╔██╗ ██║█████╗  ██║   ██║██║   ██║██║██╔████╔██║
# ██║╚██╗██║██╔══╝  ██║   ██║╚██╗ ██╔╝██║██║╚██╔╝██║
# ██║ ╚████║███████╗╚██████╔╝ ╚████╔╝ ██║██║ ╚═╝ ██║
# ╚═╝  ╚═══╝╚══════╝ ╚═════╝   ╚═══╝  ╚═╝╚═╝     ╚═╝
#
# Wrapper around nvim. Suppresses the dashboard (NO_DASHBOARD=1). Manages the IS_NVIM kitty
# window variable used by kitty's --when-focus-on to conditionally remap keys when nvim has
# focus — e.g. ctrl+page_down passes through to nvim for buffer nav instead of switching kitty
# tabs. IS_NVIM is set via iTerm2/kitty OSC escape \x1b]1337;SetUserVar=IS_NVIM=<b64>\007 where
# MQo is base64("1\n"). smart-splits.nvim also manages this via on_init/VimLeavePre autocmd,
# but the wrapper sets it before nvim starts (no gap) and unsets it after exit — even on crash,
# since exec is intentionally omitted so the script resumes and sends the unset sequence.

printf '\x1b]1337;SetUserVar=IS_NVIM=MQo\007'

if [ $# -eq 0 ]; then
    nvim
else
    NO_DASHBOARD=1 nvim -c "$*"
fi

printf '\x1b]1337;SetUserVar=IS_NVIM\007'
